    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I changed the title of this issue because we already have a `StatusButton` that aims to solve this: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/ui/shared/status/StatusButton.qml\r\n\r\nHowever, over the course of implementing this, it has grown and got a little bit out of control, so I think it's a good time clean things up a bit. Here are some things that I believe need to be revisited:\r\n\r\n- `StatusButton` has a `type` and  a `size` https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/ui/shared/status/StatusButton.qml#L9-L10. This has worked in the beginning, but it later turned out to be a burden because we've added additional types that weren't considered in the beginning. Originally it was `primary` and `secondary` to get different visuals, then later on, we added `danger` to get styles for \"delete\" buttons for example. However, both, `secondary` and `primary` button should be able to be danger buttons as well, so we had to do some rather inflexible changes in the component https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/ui/shared/status/StatusButton.qml#L84-L91\r\n- Another thing that was later taken advantage of was the `Button.flat` property to get an \"outline\" button as seen in the designs. In order to make all styles work across different variations we had ended up introducing \"quick hacks\" like `showBorder` , also `disableColorOverlay`: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/ui/shared/status/StatusButton.qml#L27-L28. We might want to consider introducing a `StatusOutlineButton` instead so we can remove a bit of complexity here\r\n- There are some state changes in place for having a `loading` state as per design https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/ui/shared/status/StatusButton.qml#L11. We might want to look into using QMLs statemachine and `PropertyChanges` instead\r\n\r\n",
